

8/22/07  Description of tests in $OPIUM/testdir
9/28/10 - updated with bi frl test

This directory contains parameter files and sample results for the following
tests.  After compiling the opium program use the script "run" to cycle
through these tests.  

al
au
b
bi
c
ca
cu
fe
h
hf
ir
la
li
mn_spd
mn_dsp
n
ne
o
p
pt
rh
s
te
ti
y_spdsp
y_ssppd

Here are some comments about each test:

1) Al - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential.  [Loginfo] keyblock is included
to show how to plot log. derivs (only works available for non-relativistic DFT psps).

2) Au - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic

3) B  - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential 

4) Bi - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, fully relativistic 

5) C  - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, finer grid

6) Ca - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, designed-non-local pseudopotential 

7) Cu - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential 

8) Fe - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, finer grid, partial core correction

9) H  - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential

10) Hf - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic

11) Ir - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, unbound f-state

12) La - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, bound f-state

13) Li - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential

14) Mn_spd, Mn_dsp - HF, optimized pseudopotential, smoothing on (3), this test exists to show that
HF psps are independent of the order of the valence orbitals.

15) N - HF, Troullier-Martins pseudopotential, smoothing on (1)

16) Ne - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential 

17) O - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, unbound d-state

18) P - HF, optimized pseudopotential, smoothing on (3)

19) Pt - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, optimized pseudopotential, scalar- relativistic, finer grid

20) Rh - DFT/ Perdew-Burke-Ernzerhof GGA, designed non-local  pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, finer grid

21) S - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, optimized pseudopotential, unbound d-state

22) Te - HF, optimized pseudopotential, smoothing on (3), scalar-relativistic

23) Ti - DFT/ Perdew-Zunger LDA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential

24) Y_spdsp, Y_ssppd - DFT/ Wu-Cohen GGA, semicore, optimized pseudopotential, scalar-relativistic, fine 
convergence tolerance, this test exists to show that DFT psps are independent of order of the valence
states.


